"source":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png","placeholder":"\/img\/avatars\/011.png"},"badges":[],"verified":1,"is_verified_user":true,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Marilia de Castro R. Pappas","affiliation":"1Plant Genetics Laboratory, Embrapa Genetic Resources and Biotechnology, Bras\u00edlia, Brazil","affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Lucileide V. Resende","affiliation":"1Plant Genetics Laboratory, Embrapa Genetic Resources and Biotechnology, Bras\u00edlia, Brazil","affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},{"name":"Dario Grattapaglia","affiliation":"1Plant Genetics Laboratory, Embrapa Genetic Resources and Biotechnology, Bras\u00edlia, Brazil","affiliations":[],"username":null,"note":null,"link":null,"image":{"source":null,"placeholder":null},"badges":[],"verified":0,"is_verified_user":false,"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false}],"versions":[],"groups":[],"is_owner":1,"has_subprotocols":0,"is_subprotocol":0,"is_bookmarked":0,"can_claim_authorship":0,"can_accept_authorship":0,"can_be_copied":1,"can_remove_fork":0,"fork_id":16135,"url":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/fast-and-inexpensive-protocols-for-consistent-extr-bkaxksfn","forks_count":{"private":0,"public":0},"access":{"can_view":1,"can_remove":1,"can_add":0,"can_edit":0,"can_publish":0,"can_get_doi":1,"can_share":1,"can_move":1,"can_move_outside":1,"can_transfer":1,"can_download":1,"is_locked":0},"guid":"881278004EA64D4BB7B41C951CA6F0D6","state_version_id":168,"steps":[{"id":1013114,"guid":"0E5FC65D924A4FB7BC21742480CC5D9E","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A27279F41E7A40A0BECEA734A40D6687","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"747D0DD50ED24FBAA485D3CCB3599556","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add an excess of sorbitol wash buffer to fill sample tubes containing macerated plant material to approximately \u00be capacity (0.9 \u2013 1.5 ml, depending on tubes used). Cap tubes and shake in the bead mill, manually or using vortex. Inspect to confirm suspension of the powdered material and shake again, if necessary.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013115,"guid":"9873823C85814293A3B2442E29C763A1","previous_id":1013114,"previous_guid":"0E5FC65D924A4FB7BC21742480CC5D9E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2E7C2CED58914C8581D6A4BAD0141167","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"746133848CDB46FEA071C776E55E61B0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 5,000-6,000 x g for three minutes at room temperature. (test new supplies\/sources of tubes to confirm they can withstand recommended speed) <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013116,"guid":"44A731E62FC746C0AF59C858ADEE6164","previous_id":1013115,"previous_guid":"9873823C85814293A3B2442E29C763A1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"59DA680A55DC4CC5A6E3EE086B1ADEDA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6DE687BD1B554BCB92DC9385915F6957","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The supernatant is decanted or aspirated from samples and discarded.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013117,"guid":"7A2CD13E2C32466D8375B2B28DA8B13F","previous_id":1013116,"previous_guid":"44A731E62FC746C0AF59C858ADEE6164","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5CDD5E2DE41D4ACD8ED8B501C5CC78CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AEF18ED393AC4D72A00AEA36CCCF3914","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">(Optional) Repeat the sorbitol wash if the supernatant from step 3 is turbid, viscous or dark with polyphenolics. Resuspend and centrifuge as before. Discard supernatant. One sorbitol wash cycle is usually sufficient with fresh, young leaf material, but can be repeated, particularly with samples especially rich in polysaccharide or tannins, judged by the clarity and color of the supernatant after centrifugation.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013118,"guid":"788FB48B204547269C5208996B6FA1B0","previous_id":1013117,"previous_guid":"7A2CD13E2C32466D8375B2B28DA8B13F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C3111370C4DD4C46BC219B426F7A12BD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0CA737D60E5B43F18B05962E8ADC7D03","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add pre-warmed extraction buffer to the sample tubes (approximately \u00bd the sample tube capacity: 650 \u00b5l in 2 ml tubes or 400 \u00b5l when for example 1.1 ml microtubes in 96-well tube racks are used).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013119,"guid":"1A8B99B1BF52488382252144E0F24BDC","previous_id":1013118,"previous_guid":"788FB48B204547269C5208996B6FA1B0","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2681322CB9B84573BED893F8391BE8D3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"500E227ED9B645998F7080450DE557CC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspend macerate samples by shaking for five seconds in the bead mill or by vortexing. The ball bearings remaining in the tubes greatly assist the macerate mixing process.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013120,"guid":"7E33650710404EDA8479CD8E7E11D0D8","previous_id":1013119,"previous_guid":"1A8B99B1BF52488382252144E0F24BDC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EF1DB218583D4FA28E5753DBEC01ED6A","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"EFADDC3155934CA7B64FB5D9A00DFB34","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Incubate samples at 65\u00b0C for a minimum of 30 minutes, up to 60 minutes, with mixing by inversion every ten minutes. Remove from water bath\/oven and allow samples to cool at room temperature for five minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013121,"guid":"A5CF4CD5DEFD4A1AA83AED0D5B2B5152","previous_id":1013120,"previous_guid":"7E33650710404EDA8479CD8E7E11D0D8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"991A789450824FC98B43750E7958983C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A084AEF68D9D4EC59F79FBAE48555B02","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add CIA to sample tubes (700 \u00b5l or fill to approximately 4\/5 tube capacity). Shake tubes vigorously for 10 seconds. This is efficiently accomplished using the bead mill if desired.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013122,"guid":"7872CA67CED64944A341B3E04C5628C9","previous_id":1013121,"previous_guid":"A5CF4CD5DEFD4A1AA83AED0D5B2B5152","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F0C1E0910FFC4760AD4AA3A1997D2349","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D48D0E729F9C4DD28A183EECA8DC0FD6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge samples at 5,000-6,000 x g for 30 minutes at room temperature. (test tubes in pilot experiments to confirm they do not rupture, especially if larger diameter ball bearings are utilized).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013123,"guid":"B743D0CA5D6D4B2AA9C35E2DEEE18C81","previous_id":1013122,"previous_guid":"7872CA67CED64944A341B3E04C5628C9","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"733319355BFD4B3BA9F2889407905B09","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7C38A9D4924C47849501F7B5FE461625","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully remove the upper aqueous phase by pipetting. In 2 ml tube extractions, 650 \u00b5l  upper phase is usually safely recoverable. Transfer to a new tube, carefully avoiding disturbance of the debris between phases.Although usually unnecessary, extraction with an equal volume of CIA, could optionally be repeated, with bead mill mixing and centrifugation at 5,000 to 13,000 x g for 10 minutes and recovery of the upper phase to a fresh tube.When using microtubes in 96-well format, the tube strips should be carefully lifted from the tube rack to allow visual monitoring of this recovery process when using multichannel pipettes.Ball bearings may be recovered in a sieve and washed thoroughly with tap water. If required, they can be made reusable by soaking in 10 % bleach for ten minutes, washing in four changes of Milli-Q quality H2O and drying at 70\u00b0C for at least one hour.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013124,"guid":"915B52BF491D40D5ACCF456C44117C60","previous_id":1013123,"previous_guid":"B743D0CA5D6D4B2AA9C35E2DEEE18C81","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6C0E2C58D2004A719E919C307D501E35","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6C905B6C83B14BC58DA799938D1E2249","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Nucleic acids are precipitated by the addition of 1\/10 volume of 3 M sodium acetate pH 5.2 and 0.66 volumes isopropanol. Mix by inverting ten times and keep at room temperature for at least one hour or overnight. Samples from herbarium material can be precipitated for up to four days to maximise recovery.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013125,"guid":"3374EE9C43D4496997D9571B5FA2705B","previous_id":1013124,"previous_guid":"915B52BF491D40D5ACCF456C44117C60","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B1F53433379F482B93D2CB083FAA1D5F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BAE85B7D32DE4DAEBF872BB438AD0C7C","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 13,000 x g for 30 minutes at room temperature. For microtubes in 96-well format the maximum allowable speed in the plate rotor should be used.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013126,"guid":"1823DB8BFB114E77BCA5C37C65535B16","previous_id":1013125,"previous_guid":"3374EE9C43D4496997D9571B5FA2705B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2589030F79FC4CC2A3BDFA2EC2975FC4","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B614B86B48244A4797439B6D480564B4","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully decant off the supernatants and drain tubes by resting inverted on paper towels.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013127,"guid":"9D93A52C6E3643448C02688C25578DED","previous_id":1013126,"previous_guid":"1823DB8BFB114E77BCA5C37C65535B16","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6B3D294AC3D64CEAA6572CF25CCB9211","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"93D90003AF69413F9ED5B3F2E6DF9BD6","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash pellets by the addition of 1 ml of 70 % ethanol. Centrifuge at 13,000 x g for 10 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013128,"guid":"05974CA2455F4AB39254D0FBC40AE70A","previous_id":1013127,"previous_guid":"9D93A52C6E3643448C02688C25578DED","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"22D181A7510E4B04A46201CDF601CA1D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"0D493F71FB4F4EE48B00AD1CE9D56EAE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully remove supernatants by aspiration to avoid loss of the nucleic acid pellet, which may be loose.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013129,"guid":"61C7DA9E119E47AA9D755B76282B1419","previous_id":1013128,"previous_guid":"05974CA2455F4AB39254D0FBC40AE70A","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E35ABAA287814B9594116292AF75BEA3","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"7C74A36F8CE14663900AFF92F9A2814B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dry open tubes at room temperature for approximately one hour or vacuum dry for 10 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013130,"guid":"AA1E6CD8972E40EE9B95296D4106166F","previous_id":1013129,"previous_guid":"61C7DA9E119E47AA9D755B76282B1419","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"20D6292719244397A34AB4CD6993A4E0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"DNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"47572E1C357540F1B53FB00A8F39A781","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Gently suspend pellets in 100 \u00b5l TE containing 0.1 mg ml-1 DNase-free RNase A and incubate tubes at 37 \u00b0C for 30 minutes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">DNA extraction notes:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">DNA purity may be conveniently estimated using a spectrophotometer, such as a Nanodrop 2000 (Thermo Scientific). DNA yield is more accurately estimated using a fluorimeter and fluorescent DNA binding dye, such as the Qubit system (Thermo Scientific). Yield may also be verified and DNA integrity checked by agarose gel electrophoresis.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For applications requiring high yields and high molecular weight genomic DNA, such as long read single molecule PacBio sequencing, several grams of fresh tissue should be macerated with a mortar and pestle in the presence of liquid nitrogen. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">The extraction protocol is scaled up to use 15-ml or 50-ml tubes or several microtubes in parallel and the DNA consolidated at the end. Gentle handling must be adopted throughout the entire procedure with no or only minor vortexing and never any repeated pipetting. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Resuspension of the tissue macerate following the sorbitol pre-washes should be carried out gently using a spatula and the final DNA precipitate recovered using a glass hook. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">DNA integrity can be estimated using pulsed-field gel electrophoresis and the adequate fraction selected for downstream sequencing using the Blue pippin DNA size selection system (BluePippin; Sage Science).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013131,"guid":"1B0F20CFA6774C02A13CA0D30A12986C","previous_id":1013130,"previous_guid":"AA1E6CD8972E40EE9B95296D4106166F","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B044EA7775B04F10AC6C2821800F5A08","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FC62FD0DB7144B99948CF0720A916FD2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">RNA extraction protocol:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">For RNA extraction, biological material was kept frozen at all times until the addition of sorbitol buffer. It is possible to freeze tubes containing samples and ball bearings at -80 oC along with the bead mill sample block, before using the bead mill, but samples are frequently found to have thawed by the end of maceration. We also tried freezing tubes in liquid nitrogen before using the bead mill, but frequently we lost samples because of broken tubes. If high throughput is not an issue, it is recommended to macerate tissues using a mortar and pestle in liquid nitrogen for RNA extraction.Each mortar\/pestle and spatula should be previously cleaned using a RNase decontamination solution, rinsed in distilled water, dried and pre-chilled in liquid N2 before grinding samples.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Before starting extraction:Preheat a water bath or incubator\/oven to 65 \u00b0C.Warm the lysis buffer at 65 \u00b0C for at least 15 minutes before pipetting\/dispensing.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Making sure to keep the tissue frozen with either liquid N2 or dry ice, transfer macerated samples into 2.0 ml tubes (if not using the bead mill).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013132,"guid":"53E18C457F4245EFB71A917F429A7CFF","previous_id":1013131,"previous_guid":"1B0F20CFA6774C02A13CA0D30A12986C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D2A01DA87AC24C399980C33E834B19B5","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"338E190640124F06B9BC986624B5AA38","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Immediately add an excess of sorbitol wash buffer to fill sample tubes containing macerated plant material to approximately \u00be capacity (0.9 \u2013 1.5 ml, depending on tubes used). Cap tubes and shake in the bead mill, using a vortex or manually. Inspect to confirm suspension of the powdered material and shake again, if necessary.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013133,"guid":"AC37025E1E7D43B4849B7479AD89320B","previous_id":1013132,"previous_guid":"53E18C457F4245EFB71A917F429A7CFF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"5B5F1A2158BB418999F728D0338BC932","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9C420F685DF04E38AA42DC3929CE7579","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge at 5,000 x g for five minutes at room temperature.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013134,"guid":"CA720992F813442086C4290267AE7BFD","previous_id":1013133,"previous_guid":"AC37025E1E7D43B4849B7479AD89320B","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"44A1B72BCC974264AAEDED548EC1B64F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"BE15496728F848CB863CE8BEBB8A7202","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The supernatant is aspirated from samples and discarded.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013135,"guid":"4D98703ACE2243DAB06C2EFE6E953EFB","previous_id":1013134,"previous_guid":"CA720992F813442086C4290267AE7BFD","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"375D3102EE1F4C6FAF1420A0C9D35026","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"68067208E17B47658A7FF4BA6A7CF4D8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Repeat the sorbitol wash (steps 1 to 3). We routinely used two rounds of the sorbitol solution wash for RNA extraction. Additional washes are unnecessary. RNA extraction is then continued as previously described.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013136,"guid":"33B41AD71B4A46DBB2F5228C39175DA3","previous_id":1013135,"previous_guid":"4D98703ACE2243DAB06C2EFE6E953EFB","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"119A1724A0B44B21B52083294CFAF4FD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"35CFA383BFD74964A81319E40EE7D32D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Quickly add 1.0 ml of the pre-warmed CTAB extraction buffer, shake vigorously and place in 65 oC water bath. The amount of tissue processed is dependent on type. Approximately 100 \u00b5g for leaves, 80 mg for cambium per microtube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013137,"guid":"75D1B6018D4E4DFABFA29BF18734AC54","previous_id":1013136,"previous_guid":"33B41AD71B4A46DBB2F5228C39175DA3","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2E7E969B91C44DE1A3D72F747169B2DD","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5F58D28709C44B2EB7F497E1B8FBC804","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add about 750 \u00b5l of chloroform and shake vigorously.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013138,"guid":"3CBACB7B348E4C4C8CD3F62931AE2412","previous_id":1013137,"previous_guid":"75D1B6018D4E4DFABFA29BF18734AC54","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"97D46BC38E76464D8BF6AC171149CB38","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"980B7920EE724748A5FFE13EF902678F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge for 10 minutes at 12,000 x g.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013139,"guid":"DB9C56D5F5284667A06839F075516629","previous_id":1013138,"previous_guid":"3CBACB7B348E4C4C8CD3F62931AE2412","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"BA7B2164CBAC4B1F98AF994C1112EA10","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FFADF5018D16483CA01A4661F6F0D8AC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully aspirate the aqueous phase and transfer to a fresh tube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013140,"guid":"78D4A23219934A92885E9685ECD44893","previous_id":1013139,"previous_guid":"DB9C56D5F5284667A06839F075516629","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2DB674D6737049C5A21C8A0E61CB8056","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"C4AAACE26B314E44871653BEA1B4D6F5","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 750 \u00b5l chloroform. Shake vigorously, centrifuge for 10 minutes at 12,000 x g.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013141,"guid":"DB6E96B7FF1245F9A91E45486E1BE26E","previous_id":1013140,"previous_guid":"78D4A23219934A92885E9685ECD44893","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"1D0FAACC3FB04F0AB49BDAF53C0571AC","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"AA2C7EA2C0FE4CABACA39EAF15853616","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully transfer aqueous phase to a fresh tube. Be sure to note the volume recovered.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013142,"guid":"66E4EF09DD0A483AA1423B6A0BF8D714","previous_id":1013141,"previous_guid":"DB6E96B7FF1245F9A91E45486E1BE26E","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D93773D0126B4D5696ADE0800144C37C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"13B6C209A26345008EAE1727B1C93193","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Place tubes on ice and add an equal volume of LiCl2:EDTA and mix well.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013143,"guid":"24F029D69F054F01A6C2789907871D44","previous_id":1013142,"previous_guid":"66E4EF09DD0A483AA1423B6A0BF8D714","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"FEB02427F1904254B505B14D51CB3625","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"661730C53F6E401F9484F537D15F85B0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Precipitate for 2 to 4 hours at -20 \u00b0C. Alternatively, precipitation can take place overnight at 4\u00b0C. However, there is an inverse relationship between quality and yield.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013144,"guid":"022AF54901BF494BA7B95646EA63067C","previous_id":1013143,"previous_guid":"24F029D69F054F01A6C2789907871D44","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0DDB437FDFD54F7C914B7DA791FEF050","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DD405636D5D24857BF0CEB60AFCEA6FC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Balance pairs of tubes with LiCl2:EDTA and centrifuge at 12,000 x g for 20 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013145,"guid":"0EBFA724B0D4415F973055E08B3272F8","previous_id":1013144,"previous_guid":"022AF54901BF494BA7B95646EA63067C","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"297D19FAEE0E4D7C9E178033FAF3F1BB","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E1D2F574F77B468CA27E617D3344F201","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Carefully remove and discard the supernatant being sure not to lose the pellet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013146,"guid":"4CDDD9AD6FB049BCADE945F9BCDD3139","previous_id":1013145,"previous_guid":"0EBFA724B0D4415F973055E08B3272F8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"6BA7CB795BE64EE18E46C367E63E0E2B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"6B383160A3FE4B2AAB1C34CE420B8196","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dissolve the pellet in 500 or 1000 \u00b5l of SSTE (depending on pellet size.) If necessary, heat in a 65 oC water bath for 2 to 10 minutes to help the pellet dissolve. Transfer to a fresh microtube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013147,"guid":"6D0839C457B148AEB1A5707A0E577AA5","previous_id":1013146,"previous_guid":"4CDDD9AD6FB049BCADE945F9BCDD3139","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0994070C37F3470C8FEF003C423D1871","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"5842B7354AF14FA0A12D9E3CC1030FDC","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Extract once with 500 \u00b5l chloroform. Shake or vortex tube before centrifuging at full speed for 5 to 7 minutes.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013148,"guid":"42CC14ACDC8A4CCEBECFF671C994F309","previous_id":1013147,"previous_guid":"6D0839C457B148AEB1A5707A0E577AA5","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"16EC1BAA325E4AF79A96872AA01A7386","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F8E7C1924CF84DB7AA4837248A874384","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove aqueous phase to new microtube.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013149,"guid":"49164F5F51C442AA859522B9B5A8D509","previous_id":1013148,"previous_guid":"42CC14ACDC8A4CCEBECFF671C994F309","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8C5E20AA94194A1C947D8D3926C61E1F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DF3D1D109CEA49E38BC2A4176265CC8B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Add 2 volumes of 95 % ethanol and precipitate for a minimum of 15 minutes at -80oC.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013150,"guid":"D2CD9A54EA67482FB509720AB4483E27","previous_id":1013149,"previous_guid":"49164F5F51C442AA859522B9B5A8D509","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"576442B3CC35483FBB6B22BCA0BC80D9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"152BBD1A97904123B230AA5727B07F86","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Centrifuge for 20 minutes at full speed to pellet the RNA. Pour off and discard supernatant being careful not to lose the pellet.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013151,"guid":"77DBE0FF1B4D4EB8A377BA1EF37B4172","previous_id":1013150,"previous_guid":"D2CD9A54EA67482FB509720AB4483E27","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CB39A86A0AF9497BA1687178DF9C78F0","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"E31FAB9A58F44C38A708E06D5316CF7A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Wash the pellets by adding 200 \u00b5l cold 70 % ethanol and centrifuge the samples at full speed for 3 to 5 minutes. Carefully aspirate supernatant as the pellets are very loose after 70 % ethanol wash.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013152,"guid":"8B079B417C3C48A9BFF78B23D314FC31","previous_id":1013151,"previous_guid":"77DBE0FF1B4D4EB8A377BA1EF37B4172","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"C63C48544740466BA5D4856CDD0D8F13","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F4A574A01A47472B8708BD68AEF183B0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Air dry the pellets by leaning the tubes open and on their sides on lab bench, do not speed vac to avoid contamination.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1013153,"guid":"7AA57442F3184EE9968CA027730777B6","previous_id":1013152,"previous_guid":"8B079B417C3C48A9BFF78B23D314FC31","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"4A91C5BEC6404A68AEE56448FD71D112","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA Extraction Protocol"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B39045DFE9ED435594D939CE3FFA3338","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">After the pellet is dry, add enough sterile MilliQ-grade, RNase free water or TE to dissolve the pellet (usually 10 to 50 \u00b5l depending on pellet size).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":null,"section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Modern genotyping techniques, such as SNP analysis and genotyping by sequencing (GBS), are hampered by poor DNA quality and purity, particularly in challenging plant and fungi species, rich in secondary metabolites. We therefore investigated the utility of a pre-wash step using a buffered sorbitol solution, prior to DNA extraction using a high salt CTAB extraction protocol, in a high throughput or miniprep setting. This pre-wash appears to remove interfering metabolites, such as polyphenols and polysaccharides, from tissue macerates. We also investigated the adaptability of the sorbitol pre-wash for RNA extraction using a lithium chloride-based protocol. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>The method was successfully applied to a variety of tissues, including leaf, cambium and fruit of diverse plant species including annual crops, forest and fruit trees as well as lyophilized fungal mycelium. We consistently obtained good yields of high purity DNA or RNA in all species tested. The protocol was validated for thousands of DNA samples by generating high data quality in dense SNP arrays. DNA extracted from <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Eucalyptus <\/span><span>spp. leaf and cambium as well as mycelium from <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Trichoderma <\/span><span>spp. was readily digested with restriction enzymes and performed consistently in AFLP assays. Scaled-up DNA extractions were also suitable for long read sequencing. Successful RNA quality control and good RNA-Seq data for <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Eucalyptus<\/span><span> and cashew confirms the effectiveness of the sorbitol buffer pre-wash combined with a high salt CTAB protocol for high quality RNA extraction.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1598367661}